The Account Aggregator framework is a secure, standardized system that enables seamless data sharing between Financial Information Providers (FIPs) and Financial Information Users (FIUs).

To initiate data sharing, users must provide explicit consent through a Consent Manager—an RBI-licensed entity that acts as the intermediary. Without this consent, no data can be accessed or shared.

```javascript
const consentRequest = {
  consentId: "abc123",
  dataRange: {
    from: "2023-01-01",
    to: "2023-12-31"
  },
  purpose: "LOAN_APPROVAL"
};
```

The framework ensures that all data transfers are encrypted end-to-end and users maintain complete control over their financial information.
